      <t:body>
         <t:listPerson>
            <t:person sex="1">
              
                  
                  <t:persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="birth">ሮስ፡ ነቢያት፡</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Ros Nabiyāt</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n2" type="birth">ራስ፡ ባንየት፡</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Rās Bānyāt</t:persName>
                  
               <t:persName>
                  <t:roleName type="title">ʾazzāž , bāḥǝr Nagāš, bǝḥt waddad </t:roleName>
               </t:persName>
                  
                  <t:nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <t:faith type="EOTC"/>
                  <t:occupation type="political">governor</t:occupation>
                 
               <t:floruit notBefore="1510" notAfter="1526">He was a prominent member of the ruling elite and nobility of the Ethiopian Empire on the eve of the Muslim invasion 
                  of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1500Ahmad">ʾAḥmad</t:persName>. 
                  He appears in the historiography of the sixteenth century with various titles. 
                  He is mentioned as <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8212RosNabi">
                     <t:roleName type="title">ʾazzāž </t:roleName> 
                  </t:persName> 
                  and governor of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5399Sabal">Šabal</t:placeName>, 
                  a small region in  <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</t:placeName>,   in <t:date>1510</t:date>. 
                  He was appointed as 
                  <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8212RosNabi">
                     <t:roleName type="title">bāḥǝr Nagāš </t:roleName>  
                  </t:persName>probably in <t:date>1524</t:date>, holding that office for two years. 
                  He appears as the only <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8212RosNabi">
                     <t:roleName type="title">bǝḥt waddad</t:roleName> 
                  </t:persName> 
                  in the 18th year of the reign of                   <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6229LebnaDe">
                     <t:roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</t:roleName>
                      Lǝbna Dǝngǝl</t:persName>,
                  in <t:date>1526</t:date>. During the Muslim war, <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8212RosNabi">Ros Nābiyāt (Rās Bānyāt) </t:persName>
                     was the first  commander of the strategic province of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2582Dawaro">Dawāro</t:placeName> where he was defeated. 
                     He also led several battles to defend the Christian kingdom from Muslims attacks.
                   
                  </t:floruit>
                  <t:death/>
                  
                  
               </t:person>  
               
